description.narrative:
The overall approach of the assignment has been premised on:
 1) an organisational development model, based on Results Based Management (RBM), focusing on how the CSOs aim to improve their capacity and seek to increase the effects and impact of their interventions, and
2) a Human Rights Based Approach as fundamental guiding principle of any assistance to the CSOs (technical support, on-distance advice and feedback, and training), as well as on how the CSOs apply HRBA in their own work. 
In Ukraine, the CSO system support has included the following: • Efficiency/systems-based audits on 9 CSOs;
• Capacity assessments (surveys and consultations) with 9 CSOs;
• Support to gender analysis in 8 CSOs;
• Gender mainstreamed results assessment framework (RAF) for 6 CSOs;
• Strategy/results assessment framework support to 5 CSOs;
• Support to HRBA work in 8 CSOs;
• Support to development of policies (anti-corruption, integrity, human resource management, HRBA, gender equality) to 6 CSOs;
• Comprehensive assessment of the media market and the value added of a media organisation;
• Support to governance structures in 10 CSOs including both management and boards.
